snippet.textDisplay:
Donate some of it to a great cause. Here is one that would love your help.
OwlThon is part of the nationwide movement known as Dance Marathon. Dance Marathon raises funds and awareness for a nonprofit organization called Children's Miracle Network Hospitals. All the funds raised by OwlThon go back to our local children's hospital, UF Health Shands in Gainsville, Florida. The funds go towards medical bills, arts and crafts for the kids stay at the hospital, research, beds for parents to sleep on while they look over their children during lengthy stays, and so much more that is needed to better the lives of sick children. This may be a long shot but due to COVID-19 and the worry for the safety of our community and the children we support who suffer from life-threatening illnesses, we had to cancel our 13.1-hour event that brings in almost $50K in donations. This money could change and save so many lives. You don't even have to donate to this cause because there are so many worthy causes out there, but sharing it with others is just as important. You can learn more at owlthonatfau.org

snippet.textDisplay: My bestfriend is one of the most amazing people I've ever met. Through saying yes and trying to meet new people he made a record label which became my family with 10+ different artists. He has saved many of our lives, mine included cause I wouldn't be here much longer with out him, and helped us to be able to see our dreams soon come true. Unfortunately through health issues, he has a skin disease, and really bad asthma, and depression, anxiety, etc. he hasn't been able to keep a job. So him, his wife, and 2 kids depend on his wife's salary to live, they are currently living with his in-laws but there's is not a lot of room so every night he has to stay at a friends house away from the people he cares about the most. He also couldn't afford his car payments so now he has to use his friends car to take his wife and kids to work and pre-school. He is truly the kindest person I've ever met and everyday he just wants whoever he's in contact with to smile. He will tell you if you don't smile today to reach out to him. There isn't a single person I think is more deserving of a blessing then him, he is blessing to everyone around him and unfortunately he's just on a streak of bad things happening to him. I love you guys and thanks for doing what you guys do and helping me seek discomfort. Say yes.

snippet.textDisplay:
IDEA FOR THE $70,000

Find a homeless person get them a small apartment and take them on their dream vacation, get them new clothes, and food to last them a while, help them find a job, etc.

Or find an exotic animal place that helps retired zoo animals that weren't in a good place and donate a bunch of money to help that place help more animals in need.

Or another option the 4ocean project, get into contact with the people who started it, and go on a trip with them to help clean the ocean and donate money to help them on their journey, I don't normally like projects that sell stuff since normally they don't actually do what they say they are, but u love this project and their goal and what their doing in general, I've been getting into the whole climate stuff and readibg into it, and I would love to see some big YouTubers such as yourself that have such an amazing goal of helping others join and help projects like this, such as Mr.beast for example raising over 20mil to plant trees I loved that and with I could help way more than just donating money or buying something, I wish u could go on a journey to do stuff like that, or at the very least get to see an inside "documentary" of what goes on since it seams so interesting, fun, and a good learning opportunity to see what's really going on. Also if you do happen to do the 4ocean find a stranger or a couple to join you on the journey.

P.S. love y'all and keep doing what ur doing you guys have amazing hearts and I love your message

Really hope you see this these are some things that I personally would love to see hapen

snippet.textDisplay:
I know this isn’t remotely related to the video, but...
To any random person reading this...
Are you feeling down? Yes? No? Either way, I hope your day can get even better!
Here are some wholesome facts to know:
Sea otters hold hands while sleeping, so they don’t drift away.
The voice actors of Mickey and Minnie got married IRL.
When elephants see us, their brains have the same reaction as ours when we see puppies. Elephants think we’re cute.
There is an island in Japan that you can visit, inhabited only by friendly bunnies.
There, did that make you feel better? Now let me tell you more.
If you feel like you are not accepted and you feel alone, you are not. There may be tons of others with the same pains as you, or even worse. Heck, maybe I could be one of them.. Anyway, to whoever is reading this, just remember. You only have one life. It’s precious. Put your hand to your chest, woah, do you feel that? A heartbeat. You have a purpose in this world. So go out and live your life.
I am not asking this to be pinned, hearted, or even to be liked, but please, if you could, try to spread this message to others. This message could maybe one day save a life. =)

snippet.textDisplay: Idea for 70k: the Yuma AZ Humane Society (HSOY). They are working toward a no-kill shelter by attaining a 90% catch-fix-release rate for stray cats.
